      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 81</em>, <em>Advanced Race Guide pg. 105</em><br/><strong>Price</strong> <img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbolN.gif\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"A PC can only purchase an animal, mount, or similar creature if its Challenge Rating is lower than that character's level; creatures with a Challenge Rating of 1 or lower are exempt from this restriction, as are horses.\"/> 300 gp (riding), <img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbolN.gif\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"A PC can only purchase an animal, mount, or similar creature if its Challenge Rating is lower than that character's level; creatures with a Challenge Rating of 1 or lower are exempt from this restriction, as are horses.\"/> 400 gp (riding, combat trained); <strong>Weight</strong> 1,200 lbs. (riding), 1,500 lbs. (riding, combat trained)</p><h2 class=\"framing\">Description</h2><p>Larger than even giant geckos, these mammoth lizards have been specifically bred to be used as mounts. Prized for their ability to run along cave ceilings and sheer walls, they require exotic saddles to ride. A riding gecko has the same statistics as a giant gecko with the giant template (see <em>Bestiary 3</em>).</p>",
